<p><b>What is the golden law of mechanics?</b> Simple mechanisms do not change the amount of work that needs to be done. A simple mechanism changes the required force and the distance traveled. As many times as you gain in strength when using a simple mechanism, you lose in the length of the path traveled, and vice versa.</p>
