<p><b>What is the fundamental law of classical mechanics?</b> The conservation of energy and Newton's second law or equations of motion, which can be obtained from Lagrange equations, are two of the fundamental laws of classical mechanics. In general, these two laws are considered separate fundamental laws.</p>
